Like this?

286
00:10:37,919 --> 00:10:38,519
Come on, turn around.

287
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:39,559
Turn around, turn around, turn around.

288
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:41,360
Hands down, and back.

289
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,320
Forty-five degrees.

290
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,840
This way, the clothes won't wrinkle easily.

291
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:48,000
There's a seven-day return policy. Come on.

292
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:50,360
The watch, ring, and necklace.

293
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:51,679
Let me, let me, let me.

294
00:10:51,919 --> 00:10:52,679
You're so clumsy.

295
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:53,840
You're going to break them.

296
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,720
Change into your own clothes.

297
00:10:57,759 --> 00:10:58,799
Let me tell you this one more time.

298
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:01,039
From now on, you must speak standard Mandarin to me.

299
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,840
You'll run into a lot of situations like this in the future.

300
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,679
The key is to talk less.

301
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:09,279
Besides, we've established a cool and aloof persona for you.

302
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:09,960
Do you understand?

303
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:10,840
I understand, bro.

304
00:11:12,279 --> 00:11:12,879
I understand, bro.

305
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:15,840
What I mean is,

306
00:11:17,639 --> 00:11:19,399
there weren't that many people today.

307
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,919
In the future, there will be more and more.

308
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,519
If they crowd you, just dodge them.

309
00:11:22,519 --> 00:11:24,080
If you fall, let someone help you up.

310
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,320
But the most important thing is not to talk.

311
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:25,879
The moment you open your mouth,

312
00:11:25,879 --> 00:11:27,279
calling people "big sis" or "little sis"...

313
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:29,080
it's just too provincial. Too provincial.

314
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,320
The kid really needs to practice her Mandarin.

315
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,200
Those clothes of yours...

316
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,200
Hang them up properly for me.

317
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,639
Don't wrinkle them, I have to return them.

318
00:11:34,799 --> 00:11:35,559
Right, right, right.

319
00:11:35,559 --> 00:11:36,039
And then,

320
00:11:36,039 --> 00:11:37,080
to your fans,

321
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:39,080
just say "Goodbye, princesses," and that's it.

322
00:11:39,279 --> 00:11:40,200
Goodbye, princesses.

323
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,320
Not a word more, no, no, no.

324
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,240
In the future, if you want to change your persona or something,

325
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,440
I'll hire a plant for you.

326
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,320
We can stage a whole "hero saves the damsel" scene.

327
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:46,879
That's not a problem either.

328
00:11:47,159 --> 00:11:47,600
Oh, right, bro.

329
00:11:48,759 --> 00:11:50,799
You said you'd help me find a cram school.

330
00:11:50,879 --> 00:11:51,840
It's been so long since I signed up.

331
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,039
I've been in the city for two months already.

332
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:53,879
When can I finally go?

333
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:54,840
Alright, alright, alright.

334
00:11:55,679 --> 00:11:57,399
Let's just finish the work we have on our hands,

335
00:11:57,399 --> 00:11:58,519
and then you can go to class, okay?

336
00:11:58,919 --> 00:11:59,320
Okay.

337
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:02,000
In a bit, I'll take you to the place you'll be staying.

338
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,559
You can't keep staying at my place forever.

339
00:12:04,799 --> 00:12:05,240
Right?

340
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,279
Thank you so much, Mac.

341
00:12:07,799 --> 00:12:08,840
You brought me to the city to make money,

342
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,399
and you're even helping me find a place.

343
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:11,399
First of all,

344
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:12,679
it's not "Maizi."

345
00:12:12,759 --> 00:12:13,679
It's Mac.

346
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,159
Mac. C.

347
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:16,879
C. Got it?

348
00:12:17,759 --> 00:12:18,360
From now on,

349
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:20,399
you just work hard with me.

350
00:12:20,759 --> 00:12:21,519
Do a good job at the events.

351
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,159
We'll make money together.

352
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,919
I'll treat you better and better in the future, don't you worry.

353
00:12:25,399 --> 00:12:26,159
Okay, Mac.

354
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,240
You're my benefactor.

355
00:12:29,679 --> 00:12:30,480
Okay, okay.

356
00:12:32,639 --> 00:12:35,080
I picked this residential complex especially for you.

357
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,039
It's almost entirely old men and old ladies.

358
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,679
The chance of a fan club emerging from this demographic...

359
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:41,759
is basically zero.

360
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:44,200
But you're famous now.

361
00:12:44,279 --> 00:12:45,600
So your safety awareness has to keep up.

362
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:46,559
Come on.

363
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:47,840
Let's see your new home.

364
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:57,159
How is it?

365
00:12:58,720 --> 00:12:59,039
Look.

366
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:00,480
Kitchen.

367
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,159
Gas.

368
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,240
Induction.

369
00:13:03,919 --> 00:13:04,679
You don't cook anyway.

370
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:06,080
Come, this is the bathroom.

371
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:10,879
A 90% new toilet, and...

372
00:13:11,519 --> 00:13:12,879
this non-partitioned bathroom.

373
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,120
This is the living room.

374
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,360
Mattress, AC.

375
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,159
Scenic balcony.

376
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,360
It has everything it should.

377
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,240
The design concept of this house...

378
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:25,799
maximizes the preservation of its original look.

379
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:27,279
Texture and style.

380
00:13:27,639 --> 00:13:28,919
It's the most popular style right now.

381
00:13:28,919 --> 00:13:30,720
Nordic industrial minimalist style.

382
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:32,879
Anyway, you...

383
00:13:34,639 --> 00:13:35,440
You, you... don't...

384
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,360
It's definitely not fully furnished yet.

385
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,039
So don't get upset.

386
00:13:40,679 --> 00:13:41,879
This house is great.

387
00:13:41,879 --> 00:13:42,960
No alkali stains at all.

388
00:13:43,519 --> 00:13:44,840
It even has an AC and a toilet.

389
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,519
I love this place so much.

390
00:13:46,519 --> 00:13:47,320
Thanks, Mac.

391
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:51,759
Here.

392
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:53,720
It's mine.

393
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:54,720
It's yours.

394
00:13:55,639 --> 00:13:58,159
I'll find you some furniture at the used market.

395
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:58,919
Thanks, Mac.

396
00:14:00,399 --> 00:14:00,919
Mac.

397
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:02,320
Thanks, Mac.

398
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:03,759
Take care.

399
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:04,919
Try not to go out.

400
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,480
If you do go out, wear a hat.

401
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,440
Hat, mask, things like that.

402
00:14:08,159 --> 00:14:08,960
Bye, Mac.

403
00:14:16,399 --> 00:14:16,879
Toilet.

404
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:42,440
Auntie Niu

405
00:14:42,559 --> 00:14:44,480
Anyway, that's the situation

406
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,320
My mom is abroad right now

407
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,519
Under professional medical care

408
00:14:48,799 --> 00:14:50,120
She's getting better

409
00:14:50,399 --> 00:14:51,879
My real aunt, my real aunt

410
00:14:51,919 --> 00:14:52,240
No

411
00:14:52,759 --> 00:14:53,799
We just haven't been in touch for a long time

412
00:14:53,799 --> 00:14:55,120
My mom probably didn't mention her. You forgot?

413
00:14:55,399 --> 00:14:56,960
Please take care of things at the neighborhood committee

414
00:14:57,559 --> 00:14:59,320
When... when she comes back and is better

415
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,080
I'll arrange it

416
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,200
We'll have a good get-together and visit you

417
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:02,679
Thanks for your trouble, Auntie Niu

418
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:03,360
Okay, okay

419
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:08,320
Oh my god

420
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:13,519
You're back

421
00:15:14,799 --> 00:15:15,159
Look

422
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:18,279
ID card

423
00:15:18,879 --> 00:15:19,759
It's a temporary one

424
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,399
I got it done

425
00:15:21,759 --> 00:15:23,440
No, but how did they just issue it to you?

426
00:15:23,759 --> 00:15:25,799
I just told the police officer I had plastic surgery

427
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:27,120
And anyway, the way I look now

428
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,200
Compared to my ID from twenty years ago

429
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,080
Looks exactly the same

430
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,519
And the fingerprints haven't changed

431
00:15:30,879 --> 00:15:31,320
See?

432
00:15:31,879 --> 00:15:33,360
This is all going too smoothly

433
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:34,919
They accepted it, right?

434
00:15:34,919 --> 00:15:36,399
It's a big world, anything is possible

435
00:15:36,679 --> 00:15:38,080
So you... you should just accept it too

436
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,360
The past is in the past

437
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,799
Just accept your new identity

438
00:15:41,399 --> 00:15:41,840
Cousin

439
00:15:42,639 --> 00:15:43,559
I am your mother

440
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:44,840
You have no manners

441
00:15:45,399 --> 00:15:46,080
Mom, I'm hungry

442
00:15:46,159 --> 00:15:47,000
Let's eat, let's eat

443
00:15:47,759 --> 00:15:48,759
Wait, I'll cook for you

444
00:15:50,039 --> 00:15:51,679
Tidy up this room for me

445
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,879
I've been gone so long and you haven't moved

446
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,440
I know, stop nagging

447
00:15:55,679 --> 00:15:57,120
With your mouth like that, you can't eat much, right?

448
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,000
I'll cook you some noodles

449
00:16:01,279 --> 00:16:02,080
Bro, are you home?

450
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:03,399
I'm downstairs at your place

451
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:04,440
Let me tell you

452
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,600
Xu Rui is really angry this time

453
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,000
I explained your family situation to her

454
00:16:08,559 --> 00:16:10,039
I know you don't really want to break up

455
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,360
But you can't just... whenever something happens

456
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,200
Think about pushing people away, you know?

457
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,360
You know that son of the Kong family

458
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,080
You two really need to talk this time

459
00:16:15,159 --> 00:16:16,759
Truly an unfilial son

460
00:16:17,039 --> 00:16:19,039
His mom has only been gone a few days

461
00:16:19,399 --> 00:16:21,320
And he brought that girl to live together

462
00:16:21,679 --> 00:16:22,639
Gone so fast

463
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,480
Pancreatic cancer, it's fast

464
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,320
Even the ancients knew

465
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:27,960
When mom dies, you mourn for three years

466
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,679
Right? That's right

467
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,120
This guy

468
00:16:30,759 --> 00:16:31,279
I think

469
00:16:31,279 --> 00:16:32,320
By this time next year

470
00:16:32,559 --> 00:16:33,519
The baby will be out

471
00:16:33,919 --> 00:16:36,200
It'll be a happy family of three again

472
00:16:36,559 --> 00:16:37,039
Kong Xiaocan

473
00:16:37,039 --> 00:16:38,039
Unfilial son

474
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,320
Your uncle!

475
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,279
Old Man Li?

476
00:16:42,639 --> 00:16:44,759
They said "your uncle"

477
00:16:44,799 --> 00:16:46,279
Not "Uncle Li"

478
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:48,759
Kong Xiaocan

479
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:49,960
Open the door, Kong Xiaocan

480
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:51,399
Open up, quick

481
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:52,919
I know you're home

482
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:53,759
Kong Xiaocan

483
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:54,720
Open the door

484
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,360
Aren't you disturbing the peace?

485
00:16:56,559 --> 00:16:56,960
Kong Xiaocan

486
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:57,320
What are you doing?

487
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:57,799
I'm asking you

488
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,000
When did my Godmother pass away?

489
00:16:59,320 --> 00:16:59,679
What?

490
00:16:59,679 --> 00:17:00,519
Who are you hiding in there?

491
00:17:00,879 --> 00:17:02,000
Come out! Who is it?

492
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:02,519
Keep your voice down

493
00:17:02,519 --> 00:17:03,039
Come out here

494
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,480
What do you mean your Godmother is gone?

495
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,240
Who is it? Hit him!

496
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:26,119
Who is she?

497
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:27,319
Kong Xiaocan, you scum.

498
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:28,359
You're two-timing scum.

499
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:29,200
Shut your mouth for a second.

500
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,400
Who told you my mom is gone?

501
00:17:32,839 --> 00:17:33,480
Your neighbor.

502
00:17:34,359 --> 00:17:35,119
Said Mom just passed away,

503
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,640
and you two are having a baby.

504
00:17:36,799 --> 00:17:37,480
Which neighbor?

505
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,279
Are they crazy?

506
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:48,359
My big mouth.

507
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:52,599
Little sister.

508
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:53,960
You've got a way with words.

509
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:55,400
Why are you cursing?

510
00:17:56,319 --> 00:17:57,359
You... didn't you curse too?

511
00:17:57,559 --> 00:17:58,400
Why can't I curse?

512
00:17:59,000 --> 00:17:59,359
I am your...

513
00:17:59,359 --> 00:18:00,640
No, no, no, cousin. You're my cousin.

514
00:18:01,279 --> 00:18:01,640
Cousin?

515
00:18:01,799 --> 00:18:02,920
Right, this is my cousin.

516
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:03,720
Cousin.

517
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:04,119
Oh, cousin.

518
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,000
Cousin.

519
00:18:05,359 --> 00:18:06,640
Wait, let me explain everything one by one.

520
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,720
First, my mom isn't gone.

521
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,920
My mom went abroad for treatment.

522
00:18:10,519 --> 00:18:11,240
She's already better.

523
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:13,400
She went to find my aunt abroad.

524
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,079
And she...

525
00:18:14,559 --> 00:18:16,079
is my aunt's daughter.

526
00:18:16,359 --> 00:18:18,359
She's back in the country staying with us for a bit.

527
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,160
Oh my god, you scared me to death.

528
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:21,279
Okay, okay, okay.

529
00:18:21,279 --> 00:18:22,759
I'm relieved to know Godmother is okay.

530
00:18:22,759 --> 00:18:24,680
If my mom were gone, wouldn't I tell you?

531
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:25,000
Would I really...

532
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,839
I shouldn't have listened to those rumors.

533
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:27,799
Exactly, what kind of person am I?

534
00:18:27,799 --> 00:18:28,640
They really talk nonsense.

535
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:29,480
I'm sorry, cousin.

536
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:30,359
I'm not usually like this.

537
00:18:30,599 --> 00:18:31,759
Usually, I'm actually quite...

538
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:35,079
I give up. My mouth hurts from talking.

539
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,960
Uh, Kong Guifang.

540
00:18:49,559 --> 00:18:50,880
Listen, let me explain.

541
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:52,000
That's a great name.

542
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:55,119
Retro.

543
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:56,599
I like it.

544
00:18:57,359 --> 00:18:58,119
So you...

545
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:00,400
Haven't you heard of Kong Guifang?

546
00:19:06,079 --> 00:19:06,720
I have.

547
00:19:07,559 --> 00:19:08,759
Cousin Kong Guifang, right?

548
00:19:08,759 --> 00:19:09,720
He mentions you all the time.

549
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:10,599
Your cousin is a great guy.

550
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,559
Uh, did you see anything else?

551
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:13,319
I did.

552
00:19:14,359 --> 00:19:15,960
May 11th birthday. Taurus.

553
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:17,359
We're a perfect match.

554
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:18,599
Let's check our compatibility later.

555
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,720
Let me introduce myself.

556
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:24,880
Hello.

557
00:19:26,119 --> 00:19:26,680
I'm Li Wai.

558
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:27,319
You go wait outside.

559
00:19:27,319 --> 00:19:28,359
I'm Xiaocan's best friend.

560
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:28,799
Get out.

561
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,640
We grew up together.

562
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:31,680
Get out. You go out first. Out.

563
00:19:32,279 --> 00:19:32,599
Cousin.

564
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:34,480
Let me tell you.

565
00:19:34,839 --> 00:19:35,759
About me borrowing money.

566
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:38,559
You must not tell my cousin.

567
00:19:39,079 --> 00:19:40,200
Because if you tell her,

568
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:40,920
she'll tell her mom.

569
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,880
Her mom will tell my mom.

570
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,680
Then my mom won't be able to focus on treatment.

571
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:45,000
Fine.

572
00:19:46,559 --> 00:19:47,119
So,

573
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:48,200
buddy.

574
00:19:48,759 --> 00:19:49,359
Let me ask you something.

575
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:50,839
Your cousin,

576
00:19:52,519 --> 00:19:53,680
does she have a boyfriend?

577
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:56,279
You've got some nerve.

578
00:19:56,279 --> 00:19:57,079
I'm warning you.

579
00:19:57,519 --> 00:19:58,920
Don't get any ideas about my cousin.

580
00:19:58,920 --> 00:19:59,640
If you dare try,

581
00:19:59,799 --> 00:20:00,559
we're done.

582
00:20:00,759 --> 00:20:01,359
Is it that serious? Why?

583
00:20:01,599 --> 00:20:02,319
She doesn't have a boyfriend.

584
00:20:02,319 --> 00:20:03,079
But she's a widow.

585
00:20:03,119 --> 00:20:03,799
She's bad luck for husbands.

586
00:20:03,839 --> 00:20:04,480
You two aren't a match.

587
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,519
You're full of crap.

588
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,680
I... I... Let me in.

589
00:20:07,519 --> 00:20:08,000
I need a drink of water.

590
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,000
If you dare, we're through.

591
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,079
Don't even think about it.

592
00:20:11,319 --> 00:20:12,079
What are you doing here?

593
00:20:13,359 --> 00:20:13,680
I...

594
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:14,720
I forgot about that.

595
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:15,400
Listen to me.

596
00:20:15,519 --> 00:20:16,799
Go apologize to Xu Rui right now.

597
00:20:17,079 --> 00:20:18,359
She's given you a way out.

598
00:20:18,359 --> 00:20:19,640
You need to take it, you know?

599
00:20:20,799 --> 00:20:21,640
I know. Stay out of it.

600
00:20:21,839 --> 00:20:22,359
Wait a minute.

601
00:20:22,599 --> 00:20:24,039
What happened to your mouth?

602
00:20:24,039 --> 00:20:24,799
Is it really inflammation?

603
00:20:25,359 --> 00:20:26,039
It's karma.

604
00:20:26,519 --> 00:20:27,200
Fresh lip fillers.

605
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:29,160
Spent half the money.

606
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:31,079
Go home and fill the other half.

607
00:20:33,039 --> 00:20:34,240
Take good care of your cousin, okay?

608
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,200
Make her feel at home.

609
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:43,559
Where's Li Wai?

610
00:20:44,319 --> 00:20:45,000
He went home.

611
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:45,839
Went home to eat.

612
00:20:46,319 --> 00:20:47,279
That brat.

613
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:48,720
Didn't even remember my name.

614
00:20:48,759 --> 00:20:50,200
I washed his undies for nothing when he was little.

615
00:20:50,359 --> 00:20:51,599
Good thing he didn't remember.

616
00:20:51,799 --> 00:20:52,599
We almost got busted.

617
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:53,920
But it's normal.

618
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,519
He called you Auntie Kong when he was little.

619
00:20:55,519 --> 00:20:56,319
Later he called you Godmother.

620
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,960
I don't know his mom's name either.

621
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:58,960
I just call her Auntie Wang.

622
00:20:59,119 --> 00:20:59,880
And you.

623
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,039
Why call me "cousin"?

624
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:02,839
If anything, call me "older cousin".

625
00:21:03,359 --> 00:21:03,759
You...

626
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,359
You almost slipped up just now.

627
00:21:05,359 --> 00:21:06,160
I was covering for you.

628
00:21:06,559 --> 00:21:07,319
It's too late now.

629
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,559
It's "cousin". It's already public.

630
00:21:11,799 --> 00:21:13,000
Wash your hands. Get ready to eat.

631
00:21:21,559 --> 00:21:22,240
Mom, I gotta say,

632
00:21:23,079 --> 00:21:24,119
this ointment works pretty well.

633
00:21:24,119 --> 00:21:25,319
It's not as swollen now, is it?

634
00:21:27,359 --> 00:21:27,920
What are you doing?

635
00:21:28,799 --> 00:21:30,240
You're not really thinking of looking for a job tomorrow, are you?

636
00:21:30,599 --> 00:21:31,279
What else should I do?

637
00:21:32,119 --> 00:21:32,720
If I don't go make money,

638
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:33,880
do you expect money to grow on trees?

639
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,960
If my mom starts earning money for the family again now,

640
00:21:43,559 --> 00:21:46,160
she'll continue to burn herself out in the kitchen,

641
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:49,200
continue to keep the house spotless,

642
00:21:49,359 --> 00:21:51,519
continue to raise that bunch of little brats

643
00:21:51,519 --> 00:21:53,079
until they're green and chubby.

644
00:21:53,279 --> 00:21:54,160
She might even...

645
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:57,079
become a mother all over again.

646
00:21:57,079 --> 00:21:57,680
Xiaocan, come here!

647
00:21:57,799 --> 00:21:58,759
Come play with your little brother!

648
00:21:58,759 --> 00:22:00,599
